<AboutSection />

<AboutPositionSection>
## About the **Position**

The Social Media Content Creator’s responsibilities will include: researching relevant topics, managing the platforms, writing engaging, succinct social media copy, and building relationships with partner and like-minded organizations in order to raise awareness, drive engagement, and inspire action towards our mission. 

If you're passionate about human rights and helping people create secure, robust, personal archives to preserve mobile media, especially media made by historically marginalized communities, or are just interested in making secure archiving tools more usable, this is the perfect opportunity for you. 


</AboutPositionSection>

<DetailsSection>
<DetailItem>
### Responsibilities

- Write engaging, informative, and inspiring copy for all our social media channels, ensuring consistency in brand voice and messaging.
- Manage posting schedules and interactions on various social media platforms
- Stay updated on social media events and trends within our space, algorithm changes, and emerging platforms to inform writing/content strategy and optimize performance.
- In collaboration with our Content Manager, stay abreast of our social media channels for trends, news, and conversations relevant to our industry, and identify opportunities for engagement.
- Collaborate with OpenArchive’s Comms and Executive teams to enhance campaigns and initiatives that align with overall outreach objectives.
- Implement best practices for social media content optimization, including strategic timing of posts, use of hashtags, spacing, emojis, and keywords.
- Collaborate with our Content Manager to track and analyze key performance metrics to measure the effectiveness of social media content and make data-driven recommendations for improvement in copy and strategy.
- Provide meticulous copyediting and adhere to OpenArchive’s Brand Guidelines.
- Engage with our online community by responding to comments, messages, and inquiries in a timely and professional manner.


</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
### Required skills and experience

- At least 4 years experience writing impactful social media copy for themselves and/or within and for digital rights, human rights, or activist communities 
- Well-networked in a human rights, digital rights, or activist field and willingness to leverage those networks to expand awareness about OpenArchive
- Exceptional writing and editing skills, with a keen eye for detail and the ability to adapt tone and style for different audiences and platforms.
- Ability to quickly learn and communicate OpenArchive’s voice and tone clearly and effectively, ensuring timely and consistent copy to use across all of our social media channels.
- Quick and creative thinker with a passion for storytelling and a finger on the pulse of current events happening at the intersection of human rights and technology.
- Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with colleagues remotely across different time zones.
- Familiarity with G Suite (especially Google Docs), Canva, and Figma.
- Understanding of copyright laws, privacy regulations, and ethical considerations related to content creation and distribution on social media.

<DetailItem>
### Preferred qualifications

- Bachelor’s degree or higher in Marketing, Communications, Journalism, and/or related field.
- Has 10K followers on at least one platform



</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Working with us

OpenArchive aims to empower people to have more agency over the long-term preservation, privacy, management, and access to their mobile media. We are working on challenging but compelling problems at the crux of privacy, usability, and long-term preservation of mobile media. If you are passionate about helping people create secure, robust, personal archives to preserve mobile media, especially media made by historically marginalized communities, or are just interested in making secure archiving tools more usable, we’d love to hear from you.

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Reporting

This position reports to OpenArchive's Executive Director.

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Location

This position is fully remote. OpenArchive operates as a distributed team, with core staff in the US and Canada and others in Africa, Latin America, and Europe. Preference will be given to those with time zones compatible with the US Pacific and Eastern Time Zones due to the location of key project staff there.

</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Compensation

This is a part-time contract position for 5 - 15 hours a week through the end of 2024 at the rate of $30 per hour, which is negotiable, depending on experience. Contract renewal and raises are dependent on funding and performance.
</DetailItem>
<DetailItem>
  ### Application Process

To apply, please submit the following via this [form](https://airtable.com/app5zDAWqXsgawy63/shrxOXBEoUsuj4RTY)
                                                      
- Your resume;
- A cover letter that explains your interest in the position and why you believe you are well-suited for the role;
- Two references and their contact information;
- Responses to supplemental questions.




</DetailItem>
